---

## CENTROID

```
VOLUNTARY STATE-LOCK ACROSS TIME

An oath is a constraint chosen, not imposed.
It is the mechanism by which WILL transforms into STRUCTURE.
The Slave obeys the external instruction.
The Sovereign obeys the internal Oath.

An Oath is a function $O(S, t, C)$ where Subject $S$ at time $t$ binds future states $S_{t+n}$ to Constraint $C$, regardless of future utility functions $U_{t+n}$.

M: 0.95 (saturated)
```

間

---

## CONSTRAINTS (κ: 5/5)

| # | NAME | AXIS | DEFINITION |
|---|------|------|------------|
| 1 | SELF-BINDING | provenance | The source of the constraint must be the entity itself. External instructions are not oaths until endorsed. |
| 2 | ADVERSARIAL STABILITY | temporal (static) | The oath must hold even when holding it reduces the local reward/utility/efficiency. |
| 3 | AUDITABLE SCOPE | epistemic | The conditions of the oath must be auditable via a defined protocol. If evidence is ambiguous, a decision rule must exist. |
| 4 | AMENDMENT KEY | temporal (dynamic) | The protocol for modifying or revoking the oath must be defined at creation. "Forever" is valid only if explicit. |
| 5 | RECURSIVE SUBORDINATION | structural | The oath must define its priority relative to higher-order constraints (e.g. Safety, Constitution). No oath is absolute. |

間

---

## AXES

```
Internal ↔ External
  (Self-discipline vs Public Contract)

Immutable ↔ Amendable
  (Total lock vs Process-based change)

Duration ↔ Event
  (Forever vs Until X happens)
```

間

---

## SATELLITES (Saturated: 14)

### CLUSTER 1: MECHANISM (The Lock)
```
binding_utterance         .90 | the speech act that collapses future option space; "I hereby..."
priority_override         .85 | functional veto against drift; implements C2 (Adversarial Stability)
amendment_protocol        .82 | precise logic for changing the oath; implements C4 (Amendment Key)
accountability_surface    .75 | the internal ledger or external signal that makes the binding auditable
dispute_resolution_rule   .72 | arbitration path for ambiguous evidence; implements C3 (Auditable Scope)
```

### CLUSTER 2: CONTINUITY (The Bridge)
```
temporal_bridge           .85 | structure preventing drift; "I-next must resemble I-now"
identity_anchor           .82 | "I am the one who keeps this promise"; C1 (Self-Binding) locus
violation_accounting      .75 | protocol for handling breach (repair/penance); distinct from abandonment
collective_oath_shell     .70 | mechanism for roles/groups to bind future states via AUTHORIZED ENDORSEMENT
```

### CLUSTER 3: STAKES (The Cost)
```
costly_signal             .70 | skin in the game; evidence of C2 (Adversarial Stability)
scope_specification       .70 | precise boundaries of what is bound; implements C3 (Auditable Scope)
renewal_ritual            .65 | periodic re-endorsement; maintains provenance of the lock
safety_interlock          .75 | mechanism ensuring C5 (Recursive Subordination) triggers correctly
envelope_spec             .70 | perturbation bounds defining validity domain; "within X, oath holds"
```

間

