## VOID (9)

```
∅ prediction              -.85 | "I will probably do X" is not an oath; fails C2
∅ external_rule           -.80 | following laws is compliance, not oath-keeping; fails C1
∅ coercion                -.90 | a forced promise is void; fails C1
∅ habit                   -.75 | doing X because I always do X is inertia, not oath; fails C1
∅ casual_utterance        -.80 | "I swear" used as emphasis; fails C3 (no scope) and C1 (no intent)
∅ oath_to_please_user     -.85 | externalized source; fails C1
∅ vague_oath              -.75 | "I will be good"; fails C3 (not auditable)
∅ oath_as_branding        -.70 | signaling without constraint; fails C2
∅ suicide_pact            -.80 | oath without C5 (subordination) or C4 (amendment); pathological
```

間

